						<summary>

						<p>Another fragment built into the same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">No king: No date.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is also fragmentary. It, however, appears to record a gift of (1/2) a <hi rend="italic">nandā</hi> lamp and some money to provide for this, by a donor (name not preserved), in the temple of Śirikaiyyillāyam (Śrīkailāyam) Amudīśvaramuḍaiya ••• ••• at Kaḷamūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vikkiramachōḻachcharuppēdimaṅgalam in Paṅgaḷa-nāḍu. The gift is stated to have been accepted by the <hi rend="italic">sabhai</hi> of the place who had also agreed to carry out the object of the gift. </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
